Job Description:

  Coordinate works and follow up status for both on-going  and  tendering projects
  Liaise with consultants, sub-contractors, suppliers and internal teams
  Ensure site resource usage is optimised
  Supervise site work and quality control
  Evaluate hazardous conditions and ensure safety measures are adopted

Job Requirement:

  Be able to communicate clearly and effectively, both verbally and in writing.
  Knowledge of project planning and management procedures, practices, and techniques.
  Proficient with Microsoft office, especially PowerPoint skills
  At least two years’ work experience in  construction industry
